- - RAILWAY_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN={See 1Password}
- - VITE_SUPABASE_URL={See Supabase}
- - SUPABASE_URL={See Supabase}
- - SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF={See Supabase}
- - SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_API_KEY={See 1Password}
- - VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY={See 1Password}
- - SUPABASE_SECRET_API_KEY={See 1Password}
- - SUPABASE_ANON={See 1Password}
- - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE={See 1Password}
- - SUPABASE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN={See 1Password}
- - SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD={See 1Password}
- - SES_ACCESS_KEY_ID
- - SES_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
- - SES_REGION
- - SES_FROM_EMAIL
- - SES_CONFIGURATION_SET
- Create tests that scan the application during pre-commit for broken links, 200, 300, 400 and 500 error codes.
- Create tests for the following when they exist:
- - Pagination
- - Search Results
- - Search & Filter Tools
- Ensure all pages, sub pages, categories, tags, search, filter, modals, panels, click to scroll events, update the URL string for bookmarking.
- Instead of a single loading symbol on a page, minimize layout shift by displaying a placeholder loader anywhere data comes from the database. So, for example, on a product page, there is a title, description, meta data, images, etc... So we need one placeholder loader for each of them. Not one for all.
